               <head>Jami' al-fava'id</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>1 copy of Jāmiʿ al-favāʾid by Kharakpat Rāy Kāyat</summary>
                  <msItem class="http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010105563 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh89005046 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh85100085 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2010106697 http://lccn.loc.gov/sh2008109077 http://lccn.loc.gov/n2013068356" n="1" xml:id="Uk_IO_Islamic_4081-item1">
                     <author>
                        <persName xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" type="alternative" key="person_f7662">Kharakpat Rāy Kāyat</persName>
                        <persName xml:lang="per" key="person_f7662" type="alternative">كهركپت راى كايت</persName>
                     </author>
                     <title xml:lang="per-Latn-x-lc" key="work_21982">Jāmiʿ al-favāʾid</title>
                     <title xml:lang="per" key="work_21982">جامع الفوائد</title>
                     <note>
                        <p>Critical commentary and abridged selections from the larger taz̲kirah of poets and Persian poetry, the Majmaʿ al-nafāʾis, by Sirāj al-Dīn ʿAlī Khān "Ārzū", compiled in 1195 / 1781 at the suggestion of Shaykh Nuṣrat Allāh (same as scribe?) due to the immense length of the original work</p>
                        <p>The author's name could also be rendered Kharakpati Rāy Kāyath (=Kāyasth)</p>
                        <p>Copied for Thakurāʾī Ūdan Singh, son of Narāyin Singh</p>
                     </note>
                     <textLang mainLang="per" xml:lang="per">Persian</textLang>
                     <note>
						</note>
